# Cloudflare Pages clean-URL fix
# Fixes: page works at /path/file.html but not at the clean /path/file URL
# 200 = rewrite (URL bar stays clean), not a redirect.
#
# NOTE on "not found" behavior: the top-level 404.html was renamed to
# 404.html.disabled. With no top-level 404.html present, Cloudflare Pages
# automatically falls back to serving index.html (200) for any request
# that doesn't match a real file — so any broken/unknown link opens the
# main page instead of an error. Real files (favicons, PDFs, sitemaps,
# every page below) are still served normally; this only affects requests
# that don't match anything. To restore a real 404 page later, rename
# 404.html.disabled back to 404.html.

